President Muhammadu Buhari, on Tuesday, October 8 will submit the 2020 Appropriation bill to the joint sittings of the National Assembly. The was contained in a letter addressed to the Speaker and read by the Speaker, Femi Gbajabiamila on Thursday. According to the letter, the President requested for 2pm on Tuesday for the budget presentation. It would be recalled that the House today passed Medium Term Expenditure Framework (MTEF), which changed the budget from the N10,002trillion to N10,729.4 trillion. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.